---
// Left-bordered editorial quote, ported from PerfManifesto in
// landing-sections.jsx.
---

<section class="nz-section" style="padding-top: 60px;">
  <div class="nz-container" style="max-width: 880px;">
    <div style="border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 28px;">
      <div class="nz-kicker" style="margin-bottom: 18px;">
        The performance obsession
      </div>
      <p class="manifesto-lead">
        Most note apps slow down once you have a few thousand notes.<br />
        <span style="color: var(--fg-mute);">NoteZ doesn't.</span>
      </p>
      <p class="manifesto-body">
        We measure every feature against one user: the one with a million notes.
        If a feature can't survive that, it doesn't ship. Searching, scrolling,
        opening, switching - all of it has to feel the same on note one and on
        note one million. So that's how we built it.
      </p>
      <p class="manifesto-tail">
        Native, lightweight, no telemetry. The whole app is about the size of a
        single photo.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .manifesto-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3vw, 40px);
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .manifesto-body {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
    margin-top: 28px;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .manifesto-tail {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--fg-mute);
    margin-top: 20px;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
</style>
